{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018qSjBXQHeWRFZeb5o4fAae","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `es-cluster-1` and `es-cluster-2` don't resolve! This is the problem. In Kubernetes, for StatefulSet DNS to work:\n1. The headless service must exist (it does)\n2. The pods must have `subdomain` set matching the service name... wait, no. For StatefulSets, when you set `serviceName: es-cluster`, the pods automatically get DNS entries.\n\nBut wait - there's a catch! For StatefulSet pods to get DNS records, the pods must be READY. Since the readiness probe is failing (because the cluster hasn't formed yet), the pods aren't considered Ready, and their DNS records aren't published to kube-dns!\nThis creates a circular dependency: pods can't form a cluster without DNS resolution, but DNS records won't be published until the pods are Ready. However, I need to reconsider this—Kubernetes actually publishes DNS records for StatefulSet pods immediately when they're scheduled and assigned an IP, regardless of readiness status, especially when `publishNotReadyAddresses` is enabled.\n\nThe real issue might be that the headless service isn't configured with this flag. I should add `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` to the service spec to ensure DNS records are created for pods even before they pass readiness checks, which would break the circular dependency and allow the cluster to bootstrap. So the DNS record exists for any pod as long as `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` is set, but without it the Endpoints only include Ready pods and DNS resolution fails. I need to update the headless service with this flag.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":604,"cache_read_input_tokens":43348,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":604},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0869a345-c252-4b9e-86f8-fe71a83a0d58","uuid":"7621498f-20e8-481c-9b22-5157a8dd2634","request_id":"req_011CcQbS5AyTdRPpzd26eNsB"}
