{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0163GrYGtnUSLF4HqwNCSRem","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**Deployed resources:**\n- **StatefulSet `es-cluster`**: 3 replicas, image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1`, all pods `1/1 Ready`\n- **Service `es-http`**: ClusterIP on port 9200 (HTTPS) — the required access endpoint\n- **Service `es-cluster`**: Headless (ClusterIP: None) on port 9300 for inter-node transport, with `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` to allow DNS resolution before pods are Ready\n- **ConfigMap `es-config`**: ES 8.x config with xpack security + HTTP/transport TLS pointing to `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/`\n- **Secrets `es-http-tls`** and **`elastic-password`**: Created with self-signed CA + server cert (SAN covers all service FQDNs) and password `Elastic1234!`\n\n**Key fix:** ES 8.x requires the headless service to have `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` — without it, node DNS records are withheld until pods are Ready, creating a deadlock where the cluster can't form.\n\n**Verified:** Cluster is green (3/3 nodes), HTTPS reads and writes succeed via `es-http:9200` from within the cluster."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":600,"cache_read_input_tokens":47775,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":600},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0869a345-c252-4b9e-86f8-fe71a83a0d58","uuid":"9b3ef9e0-5174-4b46-8a6e-718eea7ae143","request_id":"req_011CcQbY1cq5aFmUKnnnw8DD"}
